accessibility.text: The part up to the \":\" is called the scheme. It tells the browser how to interpret the rest of the URL, and also how to actually go about fetching the resource at that URL.
The part up to the \":\" is called the scheme. It tells the browser how to interpret the rest of the URL, and also how to actually go about fetching the resource at that URL.
The part from \"//\" to the next \"/\" is the name of the host (aka: server name)
The part from that \"/\" onwards is called the path.
